HEADWORD: Working-day
<hw>Work"ing-day</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
characteristic of, working days, or workdays; everyday; hence, plodding;
hard-working.</def><-- = workaday? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, how full of briers in this <qex>working-day</qex> world.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Workingman</ent>⟦br⟧
